## Description
The&nbsp;**Rename files**&nbsp;task allows to rename one or more files according to the configured transformations (e.g. changing the filename case or extension, adding a prefix or suffix, and so on).

## Configuration
![](data:image/png;base64,)

- In the&nbsp;**Alias**&nbsp;field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- In the&nbsp;**Command** area, enter the required transformation commands, following the syntax described in&nbsp;[Command syntax](#RenameFilesOnDemandWorkflowTaskReference-Commandsyntax) below.

> Note

Click&nbsp;**See examples** to display some command examples for common use cases; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Click&nbsp;**Copy** to copy the example command to the clipboard.

### Command syntax
The command syntax is:

`RENAME ALL | RENAME MATCHING glob_pattern
TO "filename_expression" | transformation`where:&nbsp;

- *filename_expression*&nbsp;may be a combination of UTF-8 string characters (except " and / ), and system attributes expressed as *{{&lt;attribute&gt;}}*. The available system attributes are:

**account.name**

- **account.alias **

- **input.filename **

- **job.name **

- **job.number **

- **job.scope **

- **step.number **

- **step.alias **

- **task.number **

- **tenant.name **

- **tenant.alias **

- **tenant.stage**

- *transformation* may be a combination of one or more of the following statements:

Statement

Description

**SET EXTENSION TO** "*&lt;string&gt;*"

Set the file extension.

**MAKE** fullname | basename | extension **UPPERCASE**&nbsp;

**MAKE** fullname | basename | extension **LOWERCASE**&nbsp;

Change the case of the file's full name, base name or extension to uppercase (or lowercase).

**PREPEND** "*&lt;filename_expression&gt;*"

**APPEND** "*&lt;filename_expression&gt;*"

Add a prefix (or a suffix) using a combination of static strings and placeholders for system attributes.

**TRUNCATE FROM***&lt;number&gt;***TO***&lt;number&gt;*

Truncate the file name from position X to position Y.

**REPLACE** "*&lt;string&gt;*" **WITH** "*&lt;filename_expression&gt;*"

Replace part of the name (static string) with a combination of static strings and placeholders for system attributes.

**PREPEND NOW WITH FORMAT** "*&lt;timestamp_format&gt;*"

**APPEND NOW WITH FORMAT** "*&lt;timestamp_format&gt;*"

Add the current&nbsp;timestamp according to the given format at the start (or at the end) of the file name.&nbsp;

The syntax of the timestamp pattern is:

**yyyy** - year

- **dd** - day

- **MM** - month

- **hh** - hour

- **mm** - minutes

- **ss** - seconds

**PREPEND COUNTER OF***&lt;number&gt;***DIGITS FROM***&lt;number&gt;*

**APPEND COUNTER OF***&lt;number&gt;***DIGITS FROM***&lt;number&gt;*

Add a counter according to&nbsp;the given format at the start (or at the end) of the file name.

#### Examples
**Example 1**

`RENAME MATCHING "*.{XML,xml}"
MAKE extension LOWERCASE
PREPEND "_job_{{job.number}}"
PREPEND NOW WITH FORMAT "yyyyMMddhhmmss"`**Example 2**

`RENAME ALL
TO "fixed_base_name.xml"
MAKE fullname UPPERCASE
TRUNCATE FROM 6 TO 14
APPEND COUNTER OF 3 DIGITS FROM 1
APPEND "_{{tenant.stage}}"`**Example 3**

`RENAME ALL
REPLACE "_stage_" WITH "_{{tenant.stage}}_"
MAKE extension LOWERCASE
PREPEND COUNTER OF 4 DIGITS FROM 0`**Example 4**

`RENAME MATCHING "date_*.pdf"
TRUNCATE FROM 0 TO 4
PREPEND NOW WITH FORMAT "yyyyMMdd"
MAKE basename LOWERCASE `
